==<span style="font-family: Akaya Telivigala;">Description</span>==
The '''Harvest of Fuel''' is a 7 day long event in which [[Object 4|Eye Fuel]] is not only more common but temporarily becomes more powerful and beneficial. During the days coming up to the holiday, various [[Object List|resources]] become more common. Entities of various types can be affected by the Eye Fuel Gas "highness" effect with this trait being shared with other Eye Fuel forms including Dark Matter Eye Fuel that loses its effects.

Entities become easier to deal with as they are less hostile thanks to the enhanced Eye Fuel. Rarer and unseen<!--Yes this is a pun--> entities that are eye themed and/or weirdcore may gain human level of sentience while being passive-neutral in nature. These entities along with [[Entity 9|Facelings]] tend to celebrate The Harvest of Fuel.

The Harvest of Fuel is not only a holiday celebrated by entities but by regular wanderers as it is considered a peaceful and prosperous time of month. Wanderers and entities alike tend to wear weirdcore-themed costumes and sometimes are seen cosplaying one another. Entities that are known to harvest objects tend to be seen less which may imply that they are busy harvesting resources in a particular area.

==<span style="font-family: Akaya Telivigala;">Calculating Next Event</span>==
The Harvest of Fuel have been observed to follow certain patterns when manifesting. As a result, many users on [[Backchat (Collaborative Log)|Backchat]] often inform users when the holiday begins.

 If the previous month was a month in Winter, the current one will be during Autumn, the next will be Summer and finally, during Spring with the cycle repeating for following years.

 The specific date in which the week manifests on can be based how frequent and abundant gathering of various resources can be within the chosen month. After reaching a "peak" in item collecting, the frequency of objects that can be casually found will stabilise and this usually signifies The Harvest of Fuel is occurring. This likely implies that The Harvest of Fuel is a sort of "Harvest Month" for all forms of objects that can be found within the Backrooms.

 If a leap year occurs, the month "closest" to February 29 gets chosen however Spring may have any month randomly selected.

==<span style="font-family: Akaya Telivigala;">Holiday Impact</span>==
<tabber>
|-| Economic=  
{{Blurimage|file=eye cookie.png|caption=<big>Eye themed cookies for sale.</big>}}
The economic impact caused by this event is noticeable. Shop themed levels may sell eye themed consumables (allergies and ingredients section will say if actual Eye Fuel will be found inside) and other related decorations.

[[Back-Flags]] has reported how during the weeks following the holiday, object's Back-Cash value tends to decrease due to the influx of how common objects become before slowly and naturally rising as objects become less common. Decorations tend to naturally inflate in cost while the main purchasers of Eye Fuel, [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]] and other closely related objects that are useful for entity purges are often bought by The Anti-Entity Group and other similar groups who tend to abuse the deflation of such goods until sellers manually inflate the prices to force such wealthy groups into buying more expensive goods.

In levels such as [[Level 51]] where wanderers can buy goods, eye themed/weirdcore goods are noticeably more expensive. In levels where objects can be bought however are devoid of such products normally, during The Harvest of Fuel they may have a few eye-themed/eye related products for sale.

|-| Survival=
During The Harvest of Fuel, Eye Fuel tends to gain an anomalous enhancement. These are:

 Becoming more frequent.

 Causing all forms to gain the psychological properties of Eye Fuel Gas.

 Affecting most entities that are normally unaffected by Eye Fuel and causing them to succumb to the addicting and pacifying nature of these enhanced objects.

While great for entity hunting or general distraction with minimal casualties. The harmful affects of Liquid Eye Fuel, Plasma Eye Fuel, some types of Dark Matter Eye Fuel remain so it is advised to deal with Object 4 with precaution.

Since Eye Fuel becomes more common, Plasma Eye Fuel in the skies of certain levels or in the neon lights of certain neon themed levels and even found in space themed levels; this makes those levels temporarily mental hazardous or have regions with mental hazards. This makes various safe levels become potentiality dangerous to stay during the duration of the week.

|-| Cultural=
{{Blurimage|file=eyehat.png|caption=<big>Hat being decorated with googly eyes.</big>}}
Without question the cultural impact is large, with many going out of their way to make contests for the strangest or best looking eye-themed clothing. The most famous being Eye-con, a contest hosted on Backchat where the winner gets paid in Back-Cash. Some clans and groups have holiday activities exclusive to them. The most well-known being groups related to the A.E.G. which celebrate by committing mass entity genocides.

Some entities are observed to have behavioural changes that stay consistent only during this holiday. Some Facelings may have enter levels with mass abundance of Eye Fuel, just to stay high. Some even do it for spiritual reasons believing that they become connected to the Backrooms during "The Week of Mass Abundance" as some Facelings call it.

Families who made bases in levels may use the week as a period to expand their shelter safely. These cultural changes tends to differ to individuals based on ideals.

|-| Environmental=
{{Blurimage|file=Eyesweirdcore.jpg|caption=<big>Only known photo of [[Level 0]] having Eye Fuel Gas.</big><br><small>Level 0 was known for not having any source of Eye Fuel.</small>}}
Level known for being devoid of Eye Fuel, may have Eye Fuel, additionally levels known for having Eye Fuel may have an increased rarity for Eye Fuel. Weirdcore levels may even leak out Eye Fuel variants into nearby levels via entrances and exits.

Sometimes, levels might be naturally have decorations for The Harvest of Fuel within areas, sometimes placed by entities with reports of naturally generated decorations existing. This implies that the Backrooms itself acknowledges that its inhabitants celebrates this harvest season. Sometimes these decorations vanish after the event, sometimes they remain.

Another strange anomaly noticed was the fact fuel for cars found in the Backrooms are likely to be anomalously replaced with Eye Fuel instead. Some viewing this bizarre trait as a form of comedy generated by the level, even if it isn't practical in the slightest. Thankfully, eyes created by Liquid Eye Fuel and any Eye Fuel found in fuel tanks will be removed after the week long event has pasted, showing signs of normality.

</tabber>

==<span style="font-family: Akaya Telivigala;">Note from M.E.G.</span>==
For wanderers new to The Harvest of Fuel, you now are informed about its properties. Any new findings can be added. Other than that, we M.E.G. wish all of you a lovely week.
